    <refname>mean1</refname>
    <refpurpose>This function is used to calculate average or mean of matrix elements.</refpurpose>
  </refnamediv>


<refsynopsisdiv>
   <title>Calling Sequence</title>
   <synopsis>
   B = mean1(A)
   
   </synopsis>
</refsynopsisdiv>

<refsection>
   <title>Parameters</title>
   <variablelist>
   <varlistentry><term>A:</term>
      <listitem><para> image matrix of the source image.</para></listitem></varlistentry>
   <varlistentry><term>B :</term>
      <listitem><para> output mean value of the matrix elements of the input image.</para></listitem></varlistentry>
   </variablelist>
</refsection>

<refsection>
   <title>Description</title>
   <para>
B = mean1(A) computes the mean of the values in A.
   </para>
   <para>
</para>
